' App 2 short sequence diagram v2 — adds long-press → choose language; tap Audio plays in selected language.
' Base: app2-sequence-diagram-short.puml. Do not modify the original.
' Re-render: plantuml -tpng app2-sequence-diagram-short-v2.puml
'
@startuml App2_Sequence_Short_V2
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFBFC
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam maxMessageSize 180
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam ParticipantPadding 24
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam Participant {
  BackgroundColor #E3F2FD
  BorderColor #1976D2
  FontColor #111111
  FontStyle normal
  FontSize 12
}
skinparam SequenceParticipant {
  BackgroundColor #E3F2FD
  BorderColor #1976D2
  FontColor #111111
  FontSize 12
}
skinparam Note {
  BackgroundColor #E8F5E9
  BorderColor #43A047
}
skinparam Title {
  FontColor #111111
  FontSize 14
}

title App 2 — Audio: default English; long-press → choose language → tap again = chosen language

participant "User"
participant "App"
participant "Cache"
participant "Engine"
participant "AWS Bedrock"
participant "Summary To Audio" as TTS
participant "ElevenLabs"

== Default: tap Audio → play in English ==
note over User, ElevenLabs: Tap Audio without long-press → plays in **English** by default.
User -> App: tap Audio
App -> Cache: get(url)

alt cache miss
  Cache --> App: miss
  App -> Engine: generate(article)
  note right of Engine: conversation.json\n+ topics.json
  Engine -> Bedrock: complete(prompt)
  Bedrock --> Engine: JSON
  Engine -> Engine: validate topics
  Engine --> App: CompanionResult
  App -> Cache: save(result)

else cache hit
  Cache --> App: cached result
end

App -> TTS: play(text: textForSpeech, effectiveLanguage)
note right of TTS: default: English. If user chose language: \ntranslate then speak in chosen language.
TTS -> ElevenLabs: generateSpeech(text, languageCode)
ElevenLabs --> TTS: audio data
TTS -> User: play audio (English by default, or chosen language)

== Optional: long-press → choose language → tap again = chosen language ==
User -> App: long press Audio
App -> User: show language picker
User -> App: select language
App -> App: store effectiveTTSLanguage
note over User, App: Next **tap Audio** plays in chosen language \n(translate if non-English, then TTS).

@enduml
